   INFORMATIONAL NOTICE — NONCLINICAL RESEARCH SCOPE

   The following notice is informational and does NOT impose a use
   restriction beyond the terms of Apache-2.0 above. It documents the
   project's research scope and the limits of what successful
   verification mathematically establishes.

   This software is an open-source verifier for cryptographic
   commitments produced by the Peptide Rx Autonomous Thesis Loop (ATL)
   protocol. Successful verification of any commitment establishes only
   the internal cryptographic consistency of the chain of custody. It
   does NOT establish, claim, or imply:

   - human safety of any peptide design referenced in the commitment
   - therapeutic efficacy for any indication
   - compliance with any regulatory framework
   - that the underlying design model is fit for any particular purpose

   Software status: EXPERIMENTAL. APIs and protocol details are subject
   to change. The cross-language byte-identical property is locked on
   the three published test vectors; everything else may be revised
   until the protocol stabilizes at v1.0.
